THE BEST GF PIZZA in TOWN!
We have been taking out  their GF pizza for 3 years!
Since my little boy has been diagnosed with Celiac Buon Gusto formerly Picazzos has been a life saver.
We like the staff, they are all friendly and very caring.
We order their GF pizza at least once-twice a week.
Their regular pizza is good too.
Their salads are goo, the broccolini is great.
They use very fresh ingredients.
The food is a bit pricey but you can taste the quality.
The only thing they could improve is the GF noodles.
My son will not eat their GF noodles, they just need a better one.
Their food is overall very good quality and tasty.
Everything is organic so it's a bit more expensive but worth it.
The portions are just right, not super big but not too small.
The place itself is nice enough and the staff is super!
I just love them for going the extra mile to always accommodate my son.
My son has Celiac and Autism so it's really hard to find food he loves.
We love that we have something good/healthy so close to home.
I recommend them to all of my friends w/ Celiac or allergies.

